China Trade Has the China trade policy had a positive effect on U.S. consumers? Chinese manufacturers' exploitation of the labor force and poor working conditions have brought criticism from the U.S. and some European organizations, particularly organized labor unions.  They contend that U.S. consumers are being offered products inferior in both quality of material and workmanship.  U.S. companies allege that, with using foreign manufacturers, consumer costs remain relatively stable with minimal degradation in quality and workmanship of the product involved.
